Create a complete Blazor Web App for building inspectors on construction sites in `/tmp/sv-8d32f53feddc46a4a1e8aee2731e315d`. This is a greenfield project — create everything from scratch.

## Key Requirements
1. Inspectors fill out safety checklists and add notes at each site visit
2. Photos are attached to inspection reports
3. Must work fully offline (construction sites have poor/no connectivity)
4. When connectivity returns, data syncs back to the server
5. Mobile-first (phones and tablets)
6. Low-latency UI — inspectors tap through checklist items quickly
7. No authentication needed

## Architecture Decisions

Use **Blazor WebAssembly (standalone)** with **PWA support** so the app runs entirely client-side and works offline. Use **IndexedDB** (via JS interop) for local storage of inspections, checklists, and photo blobs. Include a minimal ASP.NET Core Web API backend for sync.

### Project Structure
Create a solution with two projects:
- `SiteInspector.Client` — Blazor WASM PWA (the inspector-facing app)
- `SiteInspector.Server` — ASP.NET Core Web API (sync endpoint + serves the client)

Use `dotnet new` to scaffold, targeting .NET 8.

## Detailed Implementation

